Use conditional compilation or the `OnPlatform` pattern in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
public static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()
{
    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();
    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();

#if ANDROID
    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Android.AndroidNotificationService>();
#elif IOS
    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.iOS.iOSNotificationService>();
#elif WINDOWS
    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Windows.WindowsNotificationService>();
#endif

    return builder.Build();
}
```

**Key points:**

- Each platform-specific class lives under `Platforms/<platform>/` and implements `INotificationService`.
- The `#if` directives ensure only the relevant implementation is compiled per target, so no missing-type errors on other platforms.
- Use `AddSingleton` (one instance) or `AddTransient` (new instance per request) depending on your needs.

**Alternative (no `#if`):** Use partial classes or the `DeviceInfo.Platform` check at runtime, but compiler directives are preferred since they avoid shipping unused platform code.
